<tr>
<td width="3%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">8 </span></span></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" width="97%">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="6" style="font-size: xx-large;"><b>WORK PLAN</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>Describe activities that will be performed to accomplish the objectives of the proposal and support expected measurable outcomes.</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><u><b>Only grant funded activities occurring during the timeframe of the proposed project should be included. Do not include activities funded with match and/or in kind contributions.</b></u></span></span><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b> </b></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="3%">
<p class="western">Â </p>
</td>
<td width="12%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Answer: </span></span></p>
</td>
<td width="85%" valign="top">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">URBAN FARM SITES <br /> Develop sites using permaculture design: soil rehab, composting, mulching, water conservation, earth shaping, irrigation, trellises. Install plant beds (broad, narrow, field, path-side, patches) fruit orchards, grape arbors, berry &amp; vine crops, cultural gardens. Develop UFN admin &amp; mgmnt systems, website.<br /> DISTRIBUTION NETWORKS <br /> Organizing neighbor crop exchange, CSA; food &amp; bicycle carts; recruit local stores &amp; restaurants to use UFN fresh produce; skills training and employment opportunities for local residents<br /> TRAINING &amp; SERVICE LEARNING<br /> Curricula development for permaculture design &amp; applications; food systems, conservation, land rehab; sustainable living, landscaping basics; rainwater harvesting ; tool safety; composting, planting, harvesting; preparing/preserving foods; vermiculture; Students apply learned skills to work on UFN. <br /> WORKSHOPS, SEMINARS, AND SPEAKER SERIES <br /> Speaker Engagements: (1) Permaculture Design; (2) Urban Farming; (3)Healthy Nutrition<br /> </span></span></p>
</td>
